Detailed Description

Container for a message (data and object references)

A Parcel can contain both flattened data that will be unflattened on the other side of the IPC (using the various methods here for writing specific types)

 //Getter and setter function
 Parcel *pParcel = new Parcel();
 int32_t i = 2, ri;
 bool b = true, rb;

 //write primitive data to Parcel
 pParcel->write(&i, sizeof(i));
 pParcel->write(&b, sizeof(b));

 //read primitive data from Parcel
 pParcel->setDataPosition(0);
 pParcel->read(&ri, sizeof(ri));
 pParcel->read(&rb sizeof(rb));

gaia::base::Vector< T * > * gaia::core::Parcel::createTypedVectorN ( ) const

Read and return a Vector containing a particular object type from the parcel that was written with writeTypedVector() at the current dataPosition().

Returns NULL if the previously written object was NULL. The Vector must have previously been written via writeTypedVector() with the same object type.

void gaia::core::Parcel::setDataSize ( size_t  size)

Can be either smaller or larger than the current size. If larger than the current capacity, more memory will be allocated.
